---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { siteFromHost } from '../../content';
const site = siteFromHost();
const path = '/alternatives/brevo-alternative';
const title = 'Best Brevo Alternatives for Shopify in 2026';
const desc = 'Compare Brevo alternatives for Shopify by ecommerce event depth, transactional email, SMS, lifecycle automation, pricing, and operational fit.';
const tools = [
  { name: 'Klaviyo', best: 'Stores that need detailed customer and product-event segmentation', price: 'Verify current contact and feature pricing', pros: 'Deep Shopify event model and flexible behavioral flows', cons: 'More setup and potentially higher profile-based cost', source: 'https://www.klaviyo.com/pricing' },
  { name: 'Omnisend', best: 'SMB stores wanting accessible ecommerce email and SMS', price: 'Verify current contact and channel pricing', pros: 'Fast Shopify-oriented multichannel workflows', cons: 'Channel economics and list growth need governance', source: 'https://www.omnisend.com/pricing/' },
  { name: 'Drip', best: 'DTC teams focused on retention and repeat purchase', price: 'Verify current contact-based pricing', pros: 'Commerce-focused automation and reporting', cons: 'Less breadth for transactional or broader CRM requirements', source: 'https://www.drip.com/pricing' },
  { name: 'Shopify Email', best: 'Small catalogs that need native campaign simplicity', price: 'Verify current Shopify allowance and limits', pros: 'Low-friction native workflow', cons: 'Limited depth for advanced behavior and orchestration', source: 'https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing' },
  { name: 'Sequenzy', best: 'Teams that want focused lifecycle and revenue-state workflows', price: 'Verify current plan and Shopify integration coverage', pros: 'Clear sequence ownership and lifecycle orientation', cons: 'Confirm Shopify catalog, SMS, and transactional requirements', source: 'https://sequenzy.io/' },
];
const faqs = [
  { question: 'Why look for a Brevo alternative on Shopify?', answer: 'Common reasons include a need for deeper ecommerce events, more specialized retention workflows, more native Shopify behavior, or a different division between transactional and marketing email.' },
  { question: 'Is Brevo cheaper than every alternative?', answer: 'Not necessarily. Compare contacts, sends, SMS, seats, integrations, implementation time, and any separate tools. Verify current pricing rather than relying on a headline starting price.' },
  { question: 'What should a migration prove?', answer: 'A real Shopify product or order event should trigger the intended message, respect consent and suppression, stop after purchase, and be measurable against Shopify orders.' },
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <main class="container py-14 md:py-20">
    <nav class="mb-8 text-sm"><a class="link" href="/alternatives">Alternatives hub</a><span class="mx-2 text-slate-400">/</span><span class="text-slate-400">Brevo</span></nav>
    <header class="max-w-4xl"><span class="badge">Shopify platform guide</span><h1 class="hero-title mt-5">{title}</h1><p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">Brevo can be a sensible broad messaging platform, but Shopify stores sometimes need a more specialized ecommerce event model, retention workflow, or native operating experience.</p><p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-slate-300">The shortlist below separates commerce depth, multichannel speed, native simplicity, and lifecycle ownership instead of treating one platform as universally best.</p></header>
    <section class="mt-12 max-w-5xl overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08]"><table class="w-full text-left"><thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Pros</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{tools.map((tool, i) => <tr class={i === 0 ? 'highlight-row' : ''}><td class="font-semibold text-white">{tool.name}</td><td>{tool.best}</td><td>{tool.pros}</td><td>{tool.cons}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table></section>
    <section class="prose-shopify mt-14 max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Decide what Brevo is replacing</h2><p>Brevo may be handling marketing campaigns, transactional messages, SMS, or all three. Map those message classes before switching. A store can replace campaign automation while keeping a dedicated transactional provider, or move lifecycle to a commerce-focused platform while retaining Brevo for operational mail.</p><p>Use Shopify as the commercial baseline. Compare incremental orders, margin after discounts, complaints, suppression accuracy, and operator time with the numbers reported inside the platform. Attribution totals are directional evidence, not guaranteed revenue.</p>
      <h2>Platform notes</h2>{tools.map((tool, i) => <section><h3>{i + 1}. {tool.name}</h3><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {tool.best}. <strong>Pros:</strong> {tool.pros}. <strong>Cons:</strong> {tool.cons}. <strong>Pricing:</strong> {tool.price}. Check the <a href={tool.source} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official source</a> and model contacts, sends, channels, seats, integrations, and migration work.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Event test</th><td>Can the same Shopify order or product event trigger the right branch and carry the required product, customer, and consent context?</td></tr><tr><th>Ownership test</th><td>Can a marketer safely change the journey, and can engineering diagnose delivery and suppression failures?</td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}
      <h2>Migration checklist</h2><ol><li>Classify marketing, transactional, and SMS messages before exporting anything.</li><li>Export consent history, suppression state, segments, templates, event mappings, and live flow logic.</li><li>Rebuild one welcome, cart, and post-purchase path with a test Shopify catalog.</li><li>Check order-based exits, duplicate suppression, mobile rendering, unsubscribe behavior, and reporting reconciliation.</li><li>Move remaining flows in stages, keeping a written collision calendar across every active channel.</li></ol>
      <h2>Verdict</h2><p>Choose Klaviyo for deep commerce behavior, Omnisend for accessible Shopify multichannel operations, Drip for retention-led DTC programs, Shopify Email for native simplicity, and Sequenzy for focused lifecycle ownership. Stay with Brevo when its broad messaging coverage is the actual advantage. Switch only when a replacement materially improves the specific workflow that is failing.</p>
    </section>
    <FaqSection faqs={faqs} />
    <p class="mt-12 text-slate-300">Continue with the <a class="link" href="/apps">app profiles</a>, <a class="link" href="/use-cases">use cases</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides">operator guides</a>.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
